The KNICKERBOCKER. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit May 24, 1906.) No. 265. Appeal from the District Court of the United States for the Southern District of New York. Peter S. Carter, for appellant. Amos Van Etten, for appellee.

Before LACOMBE, TOWNSEND, and COXE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed with costs on opinion of District Judge (138 Fed. 148).
